PCA of full nmr dataset

QYA

2021-01-03 13:32

This RMD describes the analysis of the full NMR dataset from Jingwei (Andrew Patterson) comparing lean/obese Caucasian and Chinese individuals with n=5 stool samples analysed for each of the four groups.

This full NMR dataset contains 2073 features (bins). Note each bin is not equivalent to one metabolite. Rather, one peak covers several bins and one metabolite can contribute to more than one peak/bin, so the total number of unique metabolites is <2073.

Theme

Whitecolor="#E69F00"
Chinesecolor="#0072B2"

theme_pub<- function () { 
  theme_classic(base_size=8, base_family="Helvetica") +
  theme(axis.text = element_text(size=8, color = "black"), 
        axis.title = element_text(size=10, color="black"), 
        legend.text = element_text(size=8, color = "black"), 
        legend.title = element_text(size=10, color = "black"), 
        plot.title = element_text(size=8, color="black",hjust=0.5),
        panel.border = element_rect(color="black", size=1, fill=NA))
}

Load dataset

metadata<-read_excel("/Volumes/turnbaughlab/qb3share/qiyanang/IDEO_manuscript_Rd2/data/metabo_human_metadata.xlsx") %>% select(Group, IDEO_BMI_CLASS, Ethnicity, `NMR_ID`, `SAMPLE_ID`) %>% mutate(`NMR_ID`=as.factor(`NMR_ID`))

nmr<-read_excel("/Volumes/turnbaughlab/qb3share/qiyanang/IDEO_manuscript_Rd2/data/metabo_human_nmr_full.xlsx") %>% 
  column_to_rownames("Bin") %>% 
  t() %>%
  as.data.frame() %>%
  rownames_to_column("NMR_ID") %>%
  left_join(metadata)
## Joining, by = "NMR_ID"

PCA on all subjects

# explore prcomp output
nmr.pr <- prcomp(nmr[c(2:2074)], center=TRUE, scale= TRUE)
summary(nmr.pr)
## Importance of components:
##                            PC1     PC2      PC3      PC4      PC5     PC6
## Standard deviation     23.8430 19.9174 13.02413 12.27450 11.45129 9.93728
## Proportion of Variance  0.2742  0.1914  0.08183  0.07268  0.06326 0.04764
## Cumulative Proportion   0.2742  0.4656  0.54743  0.62011  0.68337 0.73100
##                            PC7     PC8     PC9    PC10    PC11    PC12    PC13
## Standard deviation     8.97184 8.20273 7.53520 7.22035 7.01917 6.42708 6.23204
## Proportion of Variance 0.03883 0.03246 0.02739 0.02515 0.02377 0.01993 0.01874
## Cumulative Proportion  0.76983 0.80229 0.82968 0.85483 0.87859 0.89852 0.91726
##                           PC14    PC15    PC16    PC17    PC18   PC19      PC20
## Standard deviation     6.07668 5.66197 5.54031 5.13724 4.95107 4.5765 1.354e-14
## Proportion of Variance 0.01781 0.01546 0.01481 0.01273 0.01182 0.0101 0.000e+00
## Cumulative Proportion  0.93507 0.95053 0.96534 0.97807 0.98990 1.0000 1.000e+00
screeplot(nmr.pr, type = "lines", npcs = 20, main="Screeplot")
abline(h = 1, col="red", lty=5)

# plot pca
values<-nmr.pr$x %>% as.data.frame()
results<-vegan::adonis(values ~ Ethnicity, data=nmr, method="eu", permutations=10000)
ggplot(values, aes(x=PC1, y = PC2, fill = nmr$Ethnicity)) + 
  geom_point(size=2, shape=21) +
  scale_fill_manual(values=c(White=Whitecolor, Chinese=Chinesecolor)) +
  ggtitle(paste0("p=",results$aov.tab$`Pr(>F)`,", r2=",signif(results$aov.tab$R2[1]),digits=3)) +
  xlab("PC1 (23.8% Variation Explained)") +
  ylab("PC2 (19.9% Variation Explained)") +
  theme_pub()
